<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local pointer 'pos' is declared as 'struct MHD_HTTP_Res_Header *pos;' but it is only used for read-only access (pos->kind, pos->header_size, pos->value_size, pos->header, pos->value and traversing pos->next). It could be 'const struct MHD_HTTP_Res_Header *pos', so it violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>

